\subsection{Lyot stop}
\label{subsec:LS_tol}

We test the Lyot stop alignment tolerance of the WFIRST-AFTA characterization SPLC by modeling the propagation of flat, on-axis wavefronts when the Lyot stop is translated off-center. Over 7 wavelength samples and 27 angular separations spaced at $\left(\lambda_0/D\right)/4$, we compute the azimuthally averaged contrast. Then we compute the mean and maximum increment relative to the nominal contrast values, over all those wavelengths and separations. We find that the coronagraph performance is more sensitive to horizontal than vertical Lyot stop translations (here horizontal and vertical orientations are used in the same sense as the diagram in Figure~\ref{fig:char_mask_schem}). In Table~\ref{tab:charsplc_LS_tol} we summarize the effect for horizontal translations 0.5\%, 1.0\%, and 2.0\% of the pupil diameter.

